                                <h1>PMS Mobile App</h1>
                                <p>Employee mobility is becoming increasingly more important to the modern day worker and the modern day workflow. In fact, over the past decade, mobile usage has increased by over 700% while desktop and laptop use have plateaued. To that point, approximately 81% of people in the world own a smartphone. This percentage is widely composed of millenials who represent the majority of a hotel’s customer base.</p>
                                <p>The majority of millennials say their smartphone never leaves their side for the duration of their day. This means there is a huge demand for businesses to be able to offer mobile accessibility to its customer base and its employees. In fact, over 53% of workers telecommute more than half of the work week. As for its impact on business, about three quarters of the world population open business emails on smartphones. </p>
                                <p>Finding a software solution to help your business adapt to the technological advancement of the modern-day workplace is extremely valuable. Enterprise mobility is the sharing of information across a variety of mobile devices. This allows businesses to be run from any smart device anywhere in the world. Today’s hospitality businesses must be dynamic.</p>
                                <p><apex:outputLink value="{!URLFOR($Page.BN_Data)}" target="_blank">Data rules everything</apex:outputLink>. Access, storage, and usage can’t be limited. Furthermore, data on the go gives companies an advantage. Cloud-based storage is a property manager’s best friend. Staying on top of technological trends is easier with a&nbsp;<apex:outputLink value="{!URLFOR($Page.BN_Solutions)}" target="_blank">cloud-based property management system</apex:outputLink> and will keep your property ahead of the curve. Also, property businesses need to prioritize scalability which is what Booking Ninjas excels at. We can customize our pms to fit the specific needs of your property, allowing you to hit your KPIs regularly. </p>
